# Requests del caso de uso SimulateTrigger (tRPC MUTATION). El caso central:
# evalúa el workflow → no-duplicados → crea AlertEvent + notificaciones in-app
# (atómico, UnitOfWork) → envía emails post-commit (stub que loguea).
# Requiere REST Client. Levantá la API y corré el seed:  nx serve @org/api  /  pnpm seed
# Pegá un @workflowId activo (creá+activá uno, o usá uno del seed SIN evento abierto).

@host = http://localhost:3001
@workflowId = pegar-un-workflow-id-activo

### ✅ Disparar (supera umbral) → triggered:true, duplicate:false, eventId + renderedMessage
POST {{host}}/trpc/event.simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowId": "{{workflowId}}",
  "observedValue": 95
}

### ✅ Disparar de nuevo con el evento aún abierto → triggered:true, duplicate:true (no crea otro)
POST {{host}}/trpc/event.simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowId": "{{workflowId}}",
  "observedValue": 99
}

### ✅ No dispara (valor por debajo del umbral) → triggered:false (no toca la base)
POST {{host}}/trpc/event.simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowId": "{{workflowId}}",
  "observedValue": 50
}

### ❌ workflowId inexistente → 404 NOT_FOUND
POST {{host}}/trpc/event.simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowId": "99999999-9999-4999-8999-999999999999",
  "observedValue": 95
}

### ❌ observedValue no finito → 400 (lo frena Zod)
POST {{host}}/trpc/event.simulate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "workflowId": "{{workflowId}}",
  "observedValue": "abc"
}
